<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-11-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-11-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="1463" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1463">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.00/2146.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of Nicaragua</gloss>
                                to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Translation.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Corinto</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-14">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 14, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Having been honored by the courteous hospitality of Admiral Southerland
                            on board the <hi rend="italic">California</hi>, I take pleasure in
                            sending you my most cordial greeting together with the expression of my
                            high esteem for you and for your country.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">President Díaz.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>